ddkP - move line up, deletes, move up, paste upwards
ddp - move line down, deletes, paste downwards
:!mkdir -p %:h - create file and directory if the vim file does not exist
:Explore - head to explore mode
:tabe <file> - opens a tab to edit a file
:tabn - next tab
:tabp - prev tab
:gt - go to next tab
:gT - go to previous tab
{i}gt - go to i-th tab
:noh - stops the search highlight
/ - starts searching for stuff
:tabnew - open a new tab
:Files - start searching for file names
:Ag - uses silversearcher in vim to search for line through all files

